Abstract = {{The smartphone exemplifies the rhetorical smart city movement. This
   paper examines one potential use of smartphone technology-mapping public
   transportation services in a megacity of the Global South. We examine
   the potential user impacts of introducing a smartphone-generated and
   analogue-delivered schematic bus map in Dhaka, Bangladesh. After
   distributing the map, we used a web-based survey to investigate impacts
