   India's national `smart city' agenda. My response probes the roots of
   new cities such as Dholera, arguing that beyond their connections to
   post-independence new towns, they can also be understood as the
   descendants of and heirs to colonial imperial city building. Despite the
   rhetoric put forth by political figures, designers, consultants and
   other `visionaries' and `thought leaders' who label new cities as
