   upon the recent advancement in the scholarship on urban competitiveness
   that demonstrates a clear deviation from an economic-centric approach to
   incorporate multiple dimensions of a city's progress. This study has an
   explicit concern for environmental sustainability and its relationship
   with urban competitiveness and their conceptual and methodological
   articulations. Empirically, this study measures the sustainability and
