   administrations, have allowed the adoption of ICT by municipalities in
   order to provide public services. All the foregoing constitutes a boost
   of the smart city concept, which is considered in the scientific
   literature mainly from a technical point of view, overlooking deeper
   analysis on the specific services being provided by means of smart
   technologies. The current research identifies services provided using
   smart technologies at 26 Spanish smart cities and the degree of smart
   development of those cities based on which services provide. The results
   highlight that the services most widely implemented are those that allow
   direct reductions in local administration expenditure. On the other
