Year = {{2015}},
Volume = {{90}},
Number = {{B}},
Pages = {{611-622}},
Month = {{JAN}},
Abstract = {{In this paper we put forward two ideas for monitoring the Smart Cities
   initiative in a better way. In developing the first idea, we study past
   and on-going initiatives in the field of sustainable cities and livable
   cities and their respective monitoring indicators to demonstrate that
   not only is a set of indicators needed for efficient monitoring, but
   also a final synthetic or aggregative index to visualize the
   initiative's achievements. Specifically, we propose the construction of
   synthetic indices using principal component analysis (PCA). The second
   idea attempts to anticipate the changes needed, especially with regard
   to data collection, to be introduced in current monitoring practices to
   assess a city's ``smartness{''} accurately. We propose the use of
   real-time data instead of historical statistics as the basic information
   with which to construct a set of indicators to explain the initiative. A
