   improve people's everyday lives, spawn new businesses, and make
   buildings, cities, and transport smarter. Smart things allow indeed for
   ubiquitous data collection or tracking, but these useful features are
   also examples of privacy threats that are already now limiting the
   success of the Internet of Things vision when not implemented correctly.
