Month = {{NOV}},
Abstract = {{The purpose of this work is to provide an insight for a possible
   methodology to implement demand response strategies at a city scale. The
   objective is to determine a range of values for the energy and power
   that can be made available through the large deployment of a residential
   energy management system. This work can help the distribution system
   operator to assess the impact of the usage of such technology at the
   grid level.
   The paper describes a methodology that identifies the start of operation
   cycles of appliances and other loads on a given general load diagram,
   enabling the simulation of load shifting caused by the operation of
   residential energy management systems.
