Abstract = {{Land use policy can generate substantial conflict between pro-growth and
   slow-growth interests. Based on the collaborative planning model, one of
   the many roles of the professional planner is to mediate conflict and
   generate support among fragmented interests in policy aimed at
   mitigating the effects from sprawl. The analysis uses original data
   collected from cities and towns in the state of Massachusetts. This
   study empirically tests the effect a divergence between local interest
   groups in the support for planning efforts has on the adoption of smart
