   desalination for a 100,000 population city, is a promising advanced
   integral type small reactor. The thermal hydraulic analysis code with a
   drift flux model, TASS/SMR, was developed for a conservative simulation
   of a small break loss of coolant accident in SMART. Taking into account
   SMART-specific inherent characteristics, the code adopts the
   Chexal-Lellouche correlation for a drift flux model. The capability of
   TASS/SMR code is validated using the results of the experimental data.
   The code predicts conservatively the void distribution compared with the
