   conflict in Austin in the 1980s and 1990s between pro-growth and
   anti-growth machine coalitions over urban sprawl. Around that time, the
   business community also began to focus on the redevelopment of city's
   downtown and the need to address the problems of crime and homelessness.
   By the mid 1990s, the need to clean up the streets' was increasingly
