   the Amway Center's event management challenges, the City of Orlando's
   Transportation Engineering Department utilized smart event traffic
   management techniques, which integrated the following system and plan
   components: intelligent transportation system infrastructure (software
   and hardware), traffic control device upgrades, regional planning
   efforts, and state-of-the-art safety and security protocols. These
   components also helped minimize the environmental impacts of traffic
   congestion. When designing smart event plans, it is important to
   consider high-threshold events such as the NBA All-Star Game for system
   performance and to understand the balance required for operational
   efficiency and security in today's global climate. In addition,
   infrastructure performance is critical during high-profile events so
